The Mikami clan of Mikami Shrine was a group based in {{ill|Mikami|ja|三上郷|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mikami|qq=}}, Yasu District, Ōmi Province. This clan served as the priestly lineage of [[:en:Mikami Shrine|Mikami Shrine]], historically tied to [[:en:Mount Mikami|Mount Mikami]].

Mikami Shrine claims the clan descends from [[:en:Amaterasu|Amaterasu Ōmikami]]'s third son, {{ill|Amatsuhikone|ja|天津彦根命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amatsuhikone|qq=}}, and his descendant {{ill|Ame-no-Mikage-no-Kami|ja|天之御影神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ame no Mikage no Kami|qq=}}, who is said to have descended to Mount Mikami. 

According to {{ill|Mikami Shrine Historical Examination|ja|御上神社沿革考|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mikami Shrine Historical Examination|qq=}}, Mount Mikami is believed to be the tomb of {{ill|Izanagi|ja|伊弉諾命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Izanagi|qq=}} and {{ill|Izanami|ja|伊邪那美命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Izanami|qq=}}.{{Sfn|Ōtani|1899|p=3}}

